  "prompt": "What is the best answer I can give my girl when she asks me how are you?",
  "response": "The best response depends on the context and your relationship, but here are some good options:\n\n1. Honest and sincere:\n- \"I'm good, thanks for asking. How are you?\"\n- \"I'm doing well, it's nice to hear from you.\"\n\n2. Affectionate:\n- \"I'm great now that I'm talking to you.\"\n- \"I'm better now that I get to hear your voice.\"\n\n3. Playful:\n- \"Even better now that you're here.\"\n- \"Fantastic, especially since you're checking on me.\"\n\n4. If you're not feeling great:\n- \"Honestly, I've been a bit stressed, but talking to you helps.\"\n- \"Not my best day, but I appreciate you asking.\"\n\nThe key is to be genuine, show that you value her asking, and then reciprocate by asking about her day. The most important thing is to sound natural and true to your own communication style.",
